# Debugging & Fixing Health App ‚Äî Root Cause Analysis + Fix Plan

## Root Cause Analysis (Completed)

### Bug 1 ‚Äî EDAMAM_APP_KEY has whitespace in `.env` (CRITICAL)
**File:** `server/.env` line 44  
```
EDAMAM_APP_KEY= 36ec14328ae1de0be13f3f8364720c7e	
```
There is a **leading space** and a **trailing tab character** in the value. `process.env.EDAMAM_APP_KEY` evaluates to `" 36ec14...e\t"` ‚Äî non-empty so the `if (!appKey)` guard passes, but the API call fails with a 401/403 auth error. The catch block returns the **static 150 kcal fallback** for every non-Indian food lookup.

### Bug 2 ‚Äî GEMINI_API_KEY is the placeholder string (CRITICAL)
**File:** `server/.env` line 32  
```
GEMINI_API_KEY=your_gemini_api_key_here
```
`aiAnalyzer.js` line 22 explicitly checks for this placeholder and drops into an offline fallback. All AI chat goes to the dumb fallback branch. UI shows **"Fallback AI"**.

### Bug 3 ‚Äî Fallback passes entire sentence as ONE food query (CRITICAL ‚Äî explains 85 kcal bug)
**File:** `server/utils/aiAnalyzer.js` lines 24‚Äì40  
When Gemini is absent, the code does:
```js
const results = await searchFood(message)  // message = "I ate 3 chapatis, 1 bowl dal, 100g curd"
```
This sends the **entire sentence** as a single food query. Then:
- `parseQuery("I ate 3 chapatis, 1 bowl dal, 100g curd")` ‚Äî doesn't start with a digit, returns `{ qty: 1, food: "i ate 3 chapatis, 1 bowl dal, 100g curd" }`
- The loop over `INDIAN_FOOD_UNITS` finds `"chapati"` inside the food string ‚Üí returns 1 √ó 85 = **85 kcal**
- Only `results[0]` is used ‚Äî dal and curd are completely ignored

### Bug 4 ‚Äî `parseQuery` can't handle natural language quantities (CRITICAL)
**File:** `server/utils/nutritionApi.js` line 25  
Regex: `/^([\d.]+)\s*(piece|bowl|cup|g|kg|serving|plate|slice)?\s+(.+)$/i`  
Input: `"3 chapatis"` ‚Äî matches `qty=3`, `unit=undefined`, `food="chapatis"`.  
Then checking `INDIAN_FOOD_UNITS`: `"chapatis".includes("chapati")` ‚Üí **true**, works.  
BUT: `"1 bowl dal"` ‚Üí `qty=1`, `unit="bowl"`, `food="dal"` ‚Üí works.  
**Real issue:** the function is never called with split foods in the fallback ‚Äî the full sentence bypass is the root cause (Bug 3). However plurals like "chapatis" do work via `includes()`. The parsing is adequate once we split properly.

### Bug 5 ‚Äî Gemini fallback only returns `results[0]` not all foods
**File:** `server/utils/aiAnalyzer.js` line 29  
```js
totalCalories: results[0].calories  // Only first food! Others discarded.
```
Even if `searchFood` returned multiple results (it doesn't ‚Äî it returns results for one item), only index 0 is used.

### Bug 6 ‚Äî Edamam Nutrition Analysis API called with wrong endpoint
**File:** `server/utils/nutritionApi.js` line 8  
```
EDAMAM_BASE_URL = "https://api.edamam.com/api/nutrition-data"
```
The **Nutrition Analysis API** (`nutrition-data`) requires a full ingredient text and returns totals. But the app has a **Nutrition Database / Food Search App ID & Key** (`d564f7ee`). These are **two different Edamam products** with different credentials. The `nutrition-data` endpoint will reject `d564f7ee` credentials with 401. The correct endpoint for this App ID is `https://api.edamam.com/api/food-database/v2/parser`.

